The paper deals with image aesthetics assessment using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of brain-inspired networks and the study of label-preserving transformations suggest a focus on neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the subjective nature of aesthetics ratings, which could involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
